Sentencas: In the present study a comprehensive numerical model of a planar cross-flow electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) is reported.
Titulo: Three dimensional CFD modeling and experimental validation of an electrolyte supported solid oxide fuel cell fed with methane-free biogas

Sentencas: This model is solved in a 3D environment using COMSOL Multiphysics software.
Titulo: Three dimensional CFD modeling and experimental validation of an electrolyte supported solid oxide fuel cell fed with methane-free biogas

Sentencas: To verify the simulation results, an experimental set-up of a six-cell stack was built.
Titulo: Three dimensional CFD modeling and experimental validation of an electrolyte supported solid oxide fuel cell fed with methane-free biogas

Sentencas: Cell temperature and current-voltage measurements are used for validation of the simulation results.
Titulo: Three dimensional CFD modeling and experimental validation of an electrolyte supported solid oxide fuel cell fed with methane-free biogas

Sentencas: Good agreement between the simulation results and the experimental measurements is achieved.
Titulo: Three dimensional CFD modeling and experimental validation of an electrolyte supported solid oxide fuel cell fed with methane-free biogas

Sentencas: Temperature validation in addition to the popular current/voltage validation ensures that the model performs well in predicting local processes like chemical reactions.
Titulo: Three dimensional CFD modeling and experimental validation of an electrolyte supported solid oxide fuel cell fed with methane-free biogas

Sentencas: In this study methane-free biogas (CO2 + H-2) is fed to the SOFC, and the performance of the system is investigated and explained.
Titulo: Three dimensional CFD modeling and experimental validation of an electrolyte supported solid oxide fuel cell fed with methane-free biogas

Sentencas: It is concluded that the methane-free biogas reduces the cooling air flow due to endothermic reverse water gas shift reaction and gives better current density distribution over the cell compared to hydrogen.
Titulo: Three dimensional CFD modeling and experimental validation of an electrolyte supported solid oxide fuel cell fed with methane-free biogas
